14:02.676 --> 14:05.554
You don't look so good either.

14:05.595 --> 14:06.888
SUMI: What?

14:06.930 --> 14:09.099
- What?
- SUMI: No, what did you say?

14:09.140 --> 14:11.476
PATTY: Doesn't matter. It...

14:11.518 --> 14:15.146
- (CHUCKLES): Hi.
- Hi.

14:25.115 --> 14:26.157
Hi.

14:26.199 --> 14:29.286
- Hello.
- Hi.

14:32.080 --> 14:35.584
So...

14:35.625 --> 14:37.669
um...

14:37.711 --> 14:40.171
why, um...

14:40.213 --> 14:42.924
Why-why was the lady
delivering water?

14:42.966 --> 14:47.262
Um... do you mean
why was Ms. Webster

14:47.304 --> 14:49.764
delivering water
when I first got to town,

14:49.806 --> 14:51.766
got stranded
and she picked me up?

14:51.808 --> 14:53.351
Yes. Right.

14:53.393 --> 14:57.981
Mm. Because the residents
didn't have water.

14:58.023 --> 15:00.275
They didn't have water?

15:02.110 --> 15:03.778
- That's terrible.
- Mm-hmm.

15:03.820 --> 15:07.198
And I went with Ms. Webster
on one of her deliveries,

15:07.240 --> 15:09.576
where I saw the problem
firsthand.

15:09.618 --> 15:12.662
And this all happened
before the idea

15:12.704 --> 15:13.913
for the class action occurred.

15:18.918 --> 15:21.755
- It all happened before.
- Yes.

15:21.796 --> 15:25.008
I would go so far as to say that
my interaction with Ms. Webster

15:25.050 --> 15:29.095
was the foundation for the idea
of the class action,

15:29.137 --> 15:30.847
and not a solicitation.

15:30.889 --> 15:33.850
COOPERMAN: Billy boy, it fills my heart

15:33.892 --> 15:36.061
with joy and sparkles

15:36.102 --> 15:39.230
to witness such loyalty
to a partner,

15:39.272 --> 15:43.151
even a bottle-blonde loser
ambulance chaser. (LAUGHS)

15:43.193 --> 15:45.654
Why don't you shut your
fucking trap about her.

15:45.695 --> 15:49.866
All I said was that the witness
is clearly leading

15:49.908 --> 15:51.076
her own examination.

15:51.117 --> 15:55.413
- No.
- I will allow it for now, Ms. Sen,

15:55.455 --> 15:57.874
but, Mr. McBride,

15:57.916 --> 16:00.543
you seem very distracted.

16:00.585 --> 16:03.421
(LOUD CLICKING)

16:05.215 --> 16:06.299
He abandoned me.

16:06.341 --> 16:08.718
He'll abandon you,

16:08.760 --> 16:11.763
just as he has
all those he's loved.

16:11.805 --> 16:15.266
And someday very soon,

16:15.308 --> 16:19.729
he'll die, lost and alone.

16:19.771 --> 16:24.609
A sad ending to the sad tale
of the town drunk.

16:24.651 --> 16:27.195
Amen!

16:27.237 --> 16:30.198
JUDGE: Mr. McBride!

16:37.288 --> 16:39.499
I know I never said goodbye.

16:39.541 --> 16:42.794
I didn't say goodbye either.

16:42.836 --> 16:44.879
Never said who? What?

16:44.921 --> 16:46.798
I didn't say goodbye.

16:46.840 --> 16:49.467
Billy, you know there's no price

16:49.509 --> 16:52.053
on anything you want
to do for free.

16:52.095 --> 16:54.347
That's right.

16:56.015 --> 16:57.851
That's right.

17:07.277 --> 17:08.444
Your Honor?

17:08.486 --> 17:09.529
Yeah?

17:09.570 --> 17:11.614
You see, my-my partner...

17:11.656 --> 17:15.076
You don't know...
You don't know my partner.

17:16.077 --> 17:17.619
It doesn't matter what she said

17:17.662 --> 17:19.873
or she didn't say.

17:19.914 --> 17:22.083
You know, that's not the point.

17:22.125 --> 17:24.586
What is the point, Mr. McBride?

17:27.672 --> 17:31.009
(LAUGHS SOFTLY)
Well, the point is that

17:31.050 --> 17:33.386
she saw people were suffering,

17:33.428 --> 17:36.890
and she did something
I-I can't do.

17:39.642 --> 17:41.519
They didn't have any water.

17:41.561 --> 17:43.354
And she needed to help them.

17:43.396 --> 17:46.149
JUDGE: And?

17:48.234 --> 17:51.196
(WHISPERS): No more questions?

17:51.237 --> 17:53.281
No-no more questions.

17:56.409 --> 17:58.286
Well, that was something.

17:59.871 --> 18:02.999
Take a seat, Mr. McBride.

18:17.472 --> 18:18.848
(SIGHS)

18:18.890 --> 18:21.351
JUDGE: I believe you
gave it your best shot.

18:21.392 --> 18:22.894
But...

18:22.936 --> 18:26.272
I also think
you solicited your class.

18:26.314 --> 18:27.607
(QUIETLY): Oh, shit.

18:27.649 --> 18:29.776
JUDGE: I am gonna rule
in favor of the defense

18:29.818 --> 18:31.653
and grant their motion
to dismiss.

18:31.694 --> 18:35.198
I am also going to contact
the state bar.

18:35.240 --> 18:37.909
- This kind of behavior...
- Your Honor, I'll do it for free.

18:37.951 --> 18:39.410
JUDGE: Pardon me?

18:39.452 --> 18:41.162
I said I'll do it for free.

18:41.204 --> 18:44.123
There's no prohibition against
solicitation in pro bono,

18:44.165 --> 18:45.500
so I'll do it for free.

18:50.296 --> 18:52.048
Well...

18:54.092 --> 18:56.719
As long as you don't
stand a chance

18:56.761 --> 19:00.807
of making any pecuniary gain,
congratulations.

19:00.849 --> 19:02.809
You got yourself a class.

19:02.851 --> 19:04.853
Your Honor,
you can't be serious.

19:04.894 --> 19:06.646
Take it as a win, Ms. Sen.

19:06.688 --> 19:08.815
You're not going to do better.

19:08.857 --> 19:11.776
Court dismissed.

19:11.818 --> 19:13.027
All rise.

19:19.117 --> 19:22.120
So, I'm officially suing
the water board?

19:22.161 --> 19:23.538
Yeah.

19:23.580 --> 19:25.415
I thought that went very good.

19:25.456 --> 19:27.834
- Okay.
- My God, take me.

19:32.797 --> 19:35.008
The fuck was that?
The fuck was that?

19:35.049 --> 19:36.759
- Look...
- Don't-don't say a word.

19:36.801 --> 19:38.219
Don't say a word, all right?

19:38.261 --> 19:40.305
We're making decisions
separately now as partners.

19:40.346 --> 19:42.181
Right? Again with the pro bono?

19:42.223 --> 19:43.725
- That's not what it was.
- Don't say a word.

19:43.766 --> 19:44.851
Go sleep it off.

19:44.893 --> 19:46.185
I don't want to talk
to you right now.

19:46.227 --> 19:48.354
Something's wrong here,
and I don't know what it is,

19:48.396 --> 19:49.856
but you could at least
give me a chance

19:49.898 --> 19:52.567
to fuckin' talk to you.

19:52.609 --> 19:54.027
Goddamn it.

20:09.083 --> 20:11.878
(PHONE VIBRATING)

20:24.057 --> 20:26.142
- Hey.
- BRITTANY: Hey, Billy.

20:26.184 --> 20:28.311
- Um, listen.
- Yeah.

20:28.353 --> 20:31.814
I just stopped by Denise's dorm
while I was on campus.

20:31.856 --> 20:34.817
Um, when I showed up, Denise was

20:34.859 --> 20:38.863
passed out; middle of the day.

20:38.905 --> 20:42.325
Her roommate said that
she's been drinking a lot.

20:42.367 --> 20:44.786
Like this wasn't the first time.

20:44.827 --> 20:48.623
I'm kind of worried about her.

20:48.665 --> 20:49.999
Is she there with you right now?

20:50.041 --> 20:52.460
No, I put her in the shower.

20:52.502 --> 20:54.671
Yeah, well, tell her to call me.

20:54.712 --> 20:58.466
Okay, but I mean,
you should come down here, okay?

20:58.508 --> 21:00.093
You know, talk in person.

21:00.134 --> 21:02.887
Yeah. Yeah.

21:02.929 --> 21:05.306
Hey, listen,
thanks for taking care of her, okay.

21:05.348 --> 21:06.766
Sure. Of course.

21:06.808 --> 21:08.935
What's wrong?

21:08.977 --> 21:12.897
I think I'm going crazy.

21:12.939 --> 21:14.899
I keep seeing things.

21:17.068 --> 21:19.654
I don't know if
I got a brain tumor,

21:19.696 --> 21:21.364
or I don't know
what happened to me.

21:21.406 --> 21:24.033
But I'm seeing things.
All kinds of things.

21:24.075 --> 21:25.868
Billy, you're scaring me.

21:25.910 --> 21:30.331
I'm sorry, I-I'm not trying
to scare you.

21:30.373 --> 21:33.084
I'm just trying
to tell you the truth.

21:35.920 --> 21:37.338
I love you.

21:44.512 --> 21:46.597
You don't have to say
you love me, too.

21:46.639 --> 21:48.474
I get it. It's okay.

21:51.602 --> 21:53.396
I just wanted you to know.

21:56.315 --> 21:58.276
Listen, you know I care
about you, right?

21:58.317 --> 22:00.278
Yeah.

22:02.447 --> 22:04.323
One thing at a time, okay?

22:04.365 --> 22:06.200
Your daughter needs you.

22:08.244 --> 22:09.954
Yeah, she does.

22:09.996 --> 22:13.249
Just call me when
you get back to L.A.

22:13.291 --> 22:15.877
Hey, Brittany...

22:15.918 --> 22:18.254
you hang up first, okay?

22:21.382 --> 22:23.384
(BEEPS)

22:38.691 --> 22:40.693
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:00.713 --> 23:02.882
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:08.179 --> 23:09.388
(DOOR CLOSES)

23:15.520 --> 23:17.230
(KEYS JANGLE)

23:45.967 --> 23:48.344
(EXHALES SHARPLY, SNIFFLES)

23:56.102 --> 23:58.437
(MOTORCYCLE APPROACHING)

24:12.827 --> 24:14.287
ANTON: Hey.

24:15.496 --> 24:17.290
- Finally found you.
- Yeah.

24:17.331 --> 24:19.167
I-I gave your mother my answer.

24:19.208 --> 24:22.336
Yeah, well, she didn't like
that answer.

24:22.378 --> 24:24.297
Diana doesn't do noes.

24:27.633 --> 24:29.677
(NECK CRACKING)

24:31.179 --> 24:33.014
- (GRUNTS)
- (LAUGHING)

24:33.055 --> 24:34.515
Ha!

24:36.809 --> 24:38.728
(STEPHANIE CRIES OUT)

24:40.229 --> 24:41.189
You never did fight fair!

24:41.230 --> 24:43.232
(ANTON GROANING)

24:45.610 --> 24:47.862
- Quit before I break something.
- (ANTON SCREAMS)

24:47.904 --> 24:49.947
- I hate you!
- You're such a little bitch.

24:49.989 --> 24:51.157
What'd you call me?!

24:51.199 --> 24:53.701
(BOTH GRUNTING)

24:54.952 --> 24:56.954
(PANTING)

25:00.166 --> 25:01.167
(GRUNTS)

25:11.093 --> 25:12.720
(ANTON CRIES OUT)

25:30.696 --> 25:32.698
(ENGINES REVVING)

25:36.953 --> 25:38.246
(SHOUTS)

25:53.302 --> 25:55.304
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:08.943 --> 26:10.361
Fuck you!

26:19.453 --> 26:21.455
(GROANING)

26:23.416 --> 26:25.418
(ANTON GROANING LOUDLY)

26:30.423 --> 26:32.425
(PANTING)

26:34.135 --> 26:36.137
(ANTON GROANING)

26:36.178 --> 26:37.638
(CRYING OUT)

26:39.473 --> 26:42.351
Ow! Shit.

26:42.393 --> 26:43.477
Are you okay?

26:43.519 --> 26:44.854
Yes. Fine.

26:44.895 --> 26:47.106
- You're not.
- Yes, I am.

26:47.148 --> 26:49.608
I think your arm's broken.

26:49.650 --> 26:51.402
It's not.

26:51.444 --> 26:54.155
You want a ride?

26:54.196 --> 26:55.740
No.

26:55.781 --> 26:58.075
I'm okay. Thank you.

26:58.117 --> 27:00.328
I will walk.

27:00.369 --> 27:01.579
Fuck you!

27:02.788 --> 27:04.165
(MOUTHS)

27:06.792 --> 27:08.085
Fuck out of my way!

27:12.423 --> 27:14.592
(LOUD CLANG)

27:14.633 --> 27:15.843
(ANTON GROANS)

27:25.394 --> 27:28.522
(BOTH LAUGH)

28:18.739 --> 28:20.741
(CAR HORN HONKING)

28:25.037 --> 28:27.039
- (HONKING CONTINUES)
- MAN: What are you doing?

28:29.500 --> 28:30.751
Come on, lady, move your ass!

28:30.793 --> 28:32.962
(HONKING CONTINUES)

28:33.003 --> 28:35.005
It's a parking space!

28:35.047 --> 28:37.299
(HONKING CONTINUES)

28:38.384 --> 28:41.095
Are you for real?

28:52.565 --> 28:54.400
Hey, how long
have you been out here?

28:54.442 --> 28:55.860
The hell are you doing out here?

28:55.901 --> 28:58.154
Oh! I was... (GRUNTS)

28:58.195 --> 29:00.698
I just had the most
amazing experience.

29:00.739 --> 29:02.950
- How long you been out here?
- (LAUGHING): No idea,

29:02.992 --> 29:04.952
but I was gonna leave,
but then my ex-husband

29:04.994 --> 29:06.412
was standing right there.

29:06.454 --> 29:08.581
- What was he doing here?
- And we just went for a walk,

29:08.622 --> 29:12.334
and we talked and I feel
so much better about my divorce.

29:12.376 --> 29:15.546
(GASPS) And then this man
came up from the ground

29:15.588 --> 29:18.549
like he was coming out of the
top of a submarine, and the top

29:18.591 --> 29:20.593
opened like a hatch
or something, and he goes,

29:20.634 --> 29:23.596
"Are you lost?" And I said,
"I'm actually not anymore."

29:23.637 --> 29:25.931
- Let me, let me ask you a question.
- And he was very dirty.

29:25.973 --> 29:27.224
Listen to me, listen to me.

29:27.266 --> 29:29.768
Did-did you have, like,
an alcoholic drink or something

29:29.810 --> 29:31.645
that tasted weird or did you
take some kind of medicine

29:31.687 --> 29:33.063
- or anything like that?
- No. I just...

29:33.105 --> 29:34.773
'Cause I've been having
these weird things, too,

29:34.815 --> 29:36.025
and I've been seeing shit that,

29:36.066 --> 29:38.319
uh, I-I'm not sure
is there, so...

29:38.360 --> 29:40.529
I-I just had breakfast, like...

29:40.571 --> 29:41.947
(GASPS)
Maybe it was the waffles.

29:41.989 --> 29:44.450
Well, I didn't have
any waffles, though.

29:44.492 --> 29:46.035
So what did you have?

29:46.076 --> 29:48.370
I didn't have anything.
I drank that fucking juice,

29:48.412 --> 29:49.914
a little bit of it, that's it.

29:49.955 --> 29:53.876
- I finished that juice.
- You did?

29:53.918 --> 29:57.505
- The whole thing.
- Come here.

29:57.546 --> 30:00.549
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:00.591 --> 30:03.719
<i>♪ I was all right ♪</i>

30:03.761 --> 30:06.138
<i>♪ For a while ♪</i>

30:06.180 --> 30:08.057
<i>♪ I could smile ♪</i>

30:08.098 --> 30:10.935
<i>♪ For a while ♪</i>

30:10.976 --> 30:14.855
<i>♪ But when I saw you
last night, you held... ♪</i>

30:14.897 --> 30:17.233
- You okay?
- Mm-hmm.

30:17.274 --> 30:19.985
<i>♪ And you stopped to say ♪</i>

30:20.027 --> 30:22.613
<i>♪ Hello... ♪</i>

30:22.655 --> 30:26.867
Listen now, why don't you just
go back up to the room

30:26.909 --> 30:29.078
and I'm-a come get you in
a little bit and get you home,

30:29.119 --> 30:30.621
- okay?
- Okay.

30:30.663 --> 30:33.832
I want to take a shower.
I smell like asphalt.

30:33.874 --> 30:35.000
- (CHUCKLES)
- Can you smell it?

30:35.042 --> 30:38.003
No, no, honey, no, no.

30:38.045 --> 30:41.048
- Bye.
- Yeah, bye.

30:41.090 --> 30:44.051
<i>♪ Then you ♪</i>

30:44.093 --> 30:46.637
<i>♪ Said, "So long..." ♪</i>

30:46.679 --> 30:48.639
I see your wife joined you.

30:48.681 --> 30:51.809
Well, she's not my wife, but
she did tell me what happened,

30:51.850 --> 30:55.271
and, uh, you were right,
I have been here before.

30:55.312 --> 30:57.731
So, you remembered
what I told you.

31:00.276 --> 31:02.278
Well, I know this:
if I were you,

31:02.319 --> 31:03.696
I'd talk to the kitchen staff

31:03.737 --> 31:05.155
about some
of the breakfast items

31:05.197 --> 31:07.783
'cause I think they're a little
sketchy, if you get my drift.

31:07.825 --> 31:10.035
Oh? Is there something wrong?

31:10.077 --> 31:13.414
Maybe it was an accident,
probably not.

31:13.455 --> 31:15.708
One way or the other,
you could be facing a lawsuit.

31:15.749 --> 31:17.793
(LAUGHS)

31:17.835 --> 31:20.879
I do not know
what you are implying.

31:20.921 --> 31:24.008
I think you do.

31:24.049 --> 31:25.676
I'll just leave it at that.

31:25.718 --> 31:27.344
Hmm.

31:27.386 --> 31:29.388
<i>♪ So true ♪</i>

31:29.430 --> 31:32.433
<i>♪ I love you even more ♪</i>

31:32.474 --> 31:34.852
<i>♪ Than I did before ♪</i>

31:34.893 --> 31:38.063
<i>♪ But, darling, what can I do? ♪</i>

31:38.105 --> 31:40.441
Diana, it's Joe.

31:40.482 --> 31:42.985
The little fucker knows.

31:43.027 --> 31:44.862
DIANA (ON TV): ...and boost your mood.

31:47.406 --> 31:50.534
Shake your stress...

31:50.576 --> 31:52.077
(AUDIO DISTORTS)

31:52.119 --> 31:53.954
- Patty.
- Whoa! Yes.

31:53.996 --> 31:55.581
Miss Blackwood's
ready to see you now.

31:55.623 --> 31:57.082
Okay.

31:59.585 --> 32:00.961
Okay, follow me this way,
please.

32:01.003 --> 32:02.379
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah,
all right.

32:02.421 --> 32:04.423
What are you, a compass?
Hold on.

32:09.470 --> 32:11.013
- Hi.
- Hi.

32:11.055 --> 32:12.681
- How are you? Oh.
- How've you been? Yeah.

32:12.723 --> 32:14.433
- Hi, hi.
- Thank you.

32:14.475 --> 32:16.477
Thank you so much.

32:16.518 --> 32:20.105
So do you want something to eat?
Like, a snack or juice, or...

32:20.147 --> 32:21.565
- No, I'm good, I'm good.
- (CHUCKLES) No.

32:21.607 --> 32:24.568
- Here, why don't you sit right over here.
- Okay.

32:24.610 --> 32:26.320
Well...

32:26.362 --> 32:29.239
Oh, yeah.

32:29.281 --> 32:31.492
I am so happy
that you dropped by.

32:31.533 --> 32:34.161
- What can I do for you?
- I want to talk to you

32:34.203 --> 32:36.997
about the situation
with Gloria's Restaurant.

32:37.039 --> 32:39.917
Oh, yeah, that's a,
that's a tough one.

32:39.958 --> 32:41.293
Is it?

32:41.335 --> 32:44.380
Well...

32:44.421 --> 32:47.883
Yeah, I-I, um, I talked to
my brother about it, and, um...

32:47.925 --> 32:50.969
(CHUCKLES) I really
didn't want to fire her,

32:51.011 --> 32:52.429
but it probably is for the best.

32:52.471 --> 32:54.598
Optics.

32:54.640 --> 32:57.643
- A small town.
- I thought you and your brother

32:57.685 --> 32:59.144
kept your business affairs
separate?

32:59.186 --> 33:00.938
We-we normally do,

33:00.979 --> 33:04.733
but your lawsuit has made life
complicated for everyone.

33:04.775 --> 33:06.694
Well, you should reconsider
how you mistreat your employees

33:06.735 --> 33:08.153
since they're the ones
that are suffering

33:08.195 --> 33:09.446
because of your
business practices.

33:09.488 --> 33:11.448
(LAUGHING): My business practices?

33:11.490 --> 33:14.576
What, like-like the free clinic
and the organic cafeteria?

33:14.618 --> 33:16.453
- That's... I was talking about the organic cafeteria.
- Right.

33:16.495 --> 33:18.956
- It's a problem for them, I know.
- Yeah, yeah.

33:18.997 --> 33:22.126
Look, as-as sweet
as Gloria and Violet are...

33:22.167 --> 33:25.671
And they are... I mean,
I don't fault them for taking sides,

33:25.713 --> 33:26.964
but it's a lawsuit, you know.

33:27.005 --> 33:29.049
They took a side
and we had to respond.

33:29.091 --> 33:31.301
Yeah, and your response
was shitty.

33:34.179 --> 33:36.724
Wow.

33:36.765 --> 33:39.143
You really care about them,
don't you?

33:39.184 --> 33:40.728
Okay.

33:40.769 --> 33:43.814
Just forgive me, but, um...

33:43.856 --> 33:47.401
I have something here.

33:47.443 --> 33:50.612
I just couldn't help myself.

33:50.654 --> 33:52.406
Okay, what's that?

33:52.448 --> 33:56.243
Well, I-I don't,
I don't know if you know,

33:56.285 --> 33:59.496
but, uh, I adopted my boys,

33:59.538 --> 34:01.790
and I'm very sensitive
to children who have spent time

34:01.832 --> 34:03.000
in the foster care system.

34:03.041 --> 34:05.836
- Okay.
- And who may or may not

34:05.878 --> 34:08.547
know anything about who
or where they come from.

34:10.047 --> 34:14.344
So I know that you were
in the system for years,

34:14.386 --> 34:17.514
and I had a friend of mine
from Social Services

34:17.556 --> 34:19.558
look into your history.

34:19.600 --> 34:22.643
So I don't know if you've
ever had interest in meeting

34:22.686 --> 34:24.271
or talking to your birth mom...

34:24.313 --> 34:25.606
So inappropriate.

34:25.647 --> 34:27.440
Well, I-I don't see it that way.

34:27.483 --> 34:28.859
Yeah, fuck you.

34:28.900 --> 34:31.904
I don't. Patty, th-this
information was actually

34:31.945 --> 34:33.572
- very difficult to come by.
- I don't care.

34:33.614 --> 34:36.408
Hey, Patty, Patty.

34:36.449 --> 34:39.119
I am just trying to help.

34:39.161 --> 34:42.246
Help Violet and Gloria,
that's who you help. Okay?

34:42.289 --> 34:45.292
Okay. Okay.

34:45.333 --> 34:48.253
I will talk to my brother, and
we'll see what we can do, okay?

34:48.295 --> 34:50.380
Especially about Gloria's
housing situation.

34:50.422 --> 34:52.132
- Do that.
- Okay.

34:52.174 --> 34:54.676
Would you like some of this?
It has CBD oil.

34:54.717 --> 34:56.344
I would like you
to shove that up your ass.

34:56.386 --> 34:58.222
It could help with your stress.

35:01.308 --> 35:02.893
- Did you get everything, baby?
- Yeah.

35:02.935 --> 35:04.686
You didn't leave anything
under the bed, right?

35:04.728 --> 35:07.189
- No.
- Okay.

35:07.231 --> 35:08.982
I don't want to move, Mommy.

35:09.024 --> 35:11.652
I know, baby.
I don't want to move, either.

35:26.458 --> 35:27.835
Gloria?

35:27.876 --> 35:29.169
Yeah?

35:29.211 --> 35:30.963
Hi, I have your check.

35:31.004 --> 35:34.716
My check? For what?

35:34.758 --> 35:36.969
Oh, for whatever.
Maybe you could use it

35:37.010 --> 35:38.762
as a down payment
for a little something.

35:38.804 --> 35:41.348
Something for yourself, for
the little princess over here.

35:41.390 --> 35:43.225
Condo, a new car, whatever.

35:45.227 --> 35:48.355
Holy shit. $20,000? Who...

35:48.397 --> 35:49.773
Who is it from?

35:49.815 --> 35:52.234
Don't worry about it. Enjoy.

35:56.530 --> 35:59.825
- Who was that lady?
- I don't know, baby.

35:59.867 --> 36:01.118
Come on.

36:03.120 --> 36:05.914
- (PHONE RINGING)
- Hello?

36:05.956 --> 36:07.875
Hi, uh,

36:07.916 --> 36:09.877
this is Gloria
from Gloria's Restaurant.

36:09.918 --> 36:11.503
Is this Brittany?

36:11.545 --> 36:13.297
Oh, hi. Yes.

36:13.338 --> 36:16.592
Hi. Uh, sorry to bother you,
I wasn't sure who to call...

36:16.633 --> 36:18.093
No, what's up?

36:18.135 --> 36:21.930
A woman I don't know handed me
a check for $20,000.

36:21.972 --> 36:23.348
No explanation. I mean,

36:23.390 --> 36:25.017
I'm-I'm happy
for the money, but...

36:25.058 --> 36:26.560
I don't recognize the company.

36:26.602 --> 36:28.228
- I know, baby. I know, baby.
- I'm hungry.

36:28.270 --> 36:31.148
I don't recognize the company
or why they're even paying me.

36:31.189 --> 36:33.317
Um, what's the company name?

36:33.358 --> 36:36.111
Fer-de-lance.

36:36.153 --> 36:38.780
Could you take a picture of the
check and just text it to me?

36:38.822 --> 36:39.990
Yeah, sure.

36:40.032 --> 36:42.618
It-it-it sounds weird, right?

36:42.659 --> 36:45.621
We'll look into it. Don't worry.

36:45.662 --> 36:47.122
- Okay?
- Great.

36:47.164 --> 36:48.373
- All right.
- Thanks.

36:48.415 --> 36:50.125
- Thanks, Gloria. Bye.
- Bye.

36:50.167 --> 36:51.543
DENISE: I had a bad day

36:51.585 --> 36:53.337
and a couple drinks.

36:53.378 --> 36:55.213
You're making a big deal
out of nothing.

36:55.255 --> 36:56.632
That's not nothing, okay?

36:56.673 --> 36:59.718
I just don't want you going down
the wrong road, that's all.

36:59.760 --> 37:02.346
- You of all people.
- Yeah, exactly.

37:02.387 --> 37:05.265
Look, this is how it started
for me when I was a freshman.

37:05.307 --> 37:08.685
It wasn't a problem until, you
know, it suddenly was a problem.

37:08.727 --> 37:12.731
Well, thanks for the
after-school special, guys.

37:12.773 --> 37:14.149
Are we done?

37:14.191 --> 37:16.401
Oh, can you hand me
those things there?

37:19.112 --> 37:21.073
Okay.

37:21.114 --> 37:23.325
What's up with devil bitch
pictures here?

37:23.367 --> 37:25.786
She's a fucking criminal.

37:25.827 --> 37:28.538
- You got to let it go, honey.
- How can you just let her go?

37:28.580 --> 37:31.416
- Why aren't we doing anything?
- What do you want me to do?

37:31.458 --> 37:34.294
- Well, I don't know. You're the genius fucking lawyer.
- Hey, thanks.

37:36.421 --> 37:38.757
It's sick she's not in prison.

37:38.799 --> 37:41.677
I have class.

37:41.718 --> 37:43.470
Well, see ya...

37:43.512 --> 37:45.430
if you ever decide to come back to L.A.

37:48.642 --> 37:50.310
BRITTANY: I'll keep trying.

37:50.352 --> 37:53.397
BILLY: Yeah, I appreciate it.

37:53.438 --> 37:55.399
BRITTANY: Oh, remember Gloria
from Gloria's Restaurant?

37:55.440 --> 37:56.608
Yeah, yeah.

37:56.650 --> 37:59.444
She, uh, she received
this suspicious check

37:59.486 --> 38:01.196
- for a lot of money.
- Uh-huh.

38:01.238 --> 38:03.281
I don't know, may or may not
be case-related.

38:03.323 --> 38:05.158
I'll have Marva look into it.

38:06.868 --> 38:09.204
Hey, I'm sorry
I scared you, okay?

38:12.249 --> 38:13.959
It's fine. Don't worry about it.

38:14.001 --> 38:15.836
And when I was saying
that stuff to you

38:15.877 --> 38:19.548
on the phone, I... you know,
I was just in a weird...

38:19.589 --> 38:21.383
- Billy.
- ...sort of moment.

38:21.425 --> 38:23.135
It's okay.

38:42.946 --> 38:46.158
Anybody got anything to say
about anything?

38:48.994 --> 38:51.329
Hmm?

38:51.371 --> 38:54.332
Got a black eye here,

38:54.374 --> 38:56.460
arm cast. (CHUCKLES)

38:56.501 --> 38:59.129
I know there's a story
behind that.

38:59.171 --> 39:03.008
Hmm? No? Diana?

39:03.050 --> 39:05.844
You got anything?

39:05.886 --> 39:08.305
Why don't you tell us
about your day.

39:10.974 --> 39:13.435
Well, my day,

39:13.477 --> 39:16.396
my day was uneventful.

39:16.438 --> 39:18.982
Visiting a movie set

39:19.024 --> 39:20.650
was uneventful?

39:23.904 --> 39:27.282
(LAUGHS)
You talked to Stephanie?

39:27.324 --> 39:29.868
Mm-hmm. Now I get it.

39:29.910 --> 39:31.328
- Do you?
- Yeah.

39:31.369 --> 39:34.998
Oh, yeah.
Let's talk about it later.

39:35.040 --> 39:37.000
You're making plans
for our future,

39:37.042 --> 39:39.044
that seems like
a family discussion.

39:41.630 --> 39:43.757
Okay,

39:43.799 --> 39:45.967
then let's talk about it now.

39:46.009 --> 39:47.969
Actually, no, I don't,
I don't feel like it.

39:48.011 --> 39:49.805
I think I'm gonna go to bed.

39:49.846 --> 39:51.807
Mom, what about
the cake and gifts?

39:51.848 --> 39:52.974
I don't really feel
like that either.

39:53.016 --> 39:55.185
Then what the fuck
do you feel like?!

39:55.227 --> 39:58.271
I feel fucking betrayed.

39:58.313 --> 40:00.524
Gosh, that feels bad,
doesn't it?

40:00.565 --> 40:02.943
(LAUGHING): What, are you gonna
teach me a lesson?

40:02.984 --> 40:06.071
Oh, no. Oh, no.
Old dogs and all that shit.

40:06.113 --> 40:08.365
- No, no, no.
- You can be, you can be a fucking spiteful prick.

40:08.406 --> 40:10.742
Let me ask you something.

40:10.784 --> 40:14.496
When you offered to buy
Roy's land from Stephanie,

40:14.538 --> 40:17.124
whose money were you
planning on using?

40:17.165 --> 40:19.584
Every fucking penny
I made for years.

40:19.626 --> 40:21.837
I will gladly cut you a check
right now

40:21.878 --> 40:24.381
- for services rendered!
- Approaching Stephanie

40:24.422 --> 40:27.592
should've been a discussion
between the two of us,

40:27.634 --> 40:29.553
as a team.
Stop that, Anton!

40:29.594 --> 40:31.888
I do not remember my phone
ringing off the wall

40:31.930 --> 40:33.223
when you talked to her!

40:33.265 --> 40:35.934
Maybe I was going
to surprise you!

40:35.976 --> 40:40.063
Maybe I was going to give you
the signed deed as a gift.

40:40.105 --> 40:42.774
- BLACKWOOD: Maybe, maybe. It's always maybe...
- Because I love you,

40:42.816 --> 40:44.151
- I was gonna...
- ...maybe with you!

40:45.527 --> 40:47.571
Now let me tell you something!

40:47.612 --> 40:49.114
All right.

40:49.156 --> 40:52.367
You let me handle Roy's land.

40:54.452 --> 40:58.498
After the way he went
out of this world,

40:58.540 --> 41:00.959
that's the least you can do.

42:14.449 --> 42:16.409
(EXHALES)

42:16.451 --> 42:18.995
I love both of you very much.

42:20.247 --> 42:22.290
But you have both
disappointed me,

42:22.332 --> 42:25.710
and that cannot go unpunished.

42:25.752 --> 42:28.588
So, I need both of you
to tell me what you did.

42:28.630 --> 42:30.882
Okay?

42:30.924 --> 42:33.134
And why you're making me
punish both of you.

42:51.236 --> 42:53.238
I failed you.

42:53.280 --> 42:54.489
And?

42:54.531 --> 42:57.492
It won't happen again.

42:57.534 --> 42:59.828
(SIGHS)

42:59.869 --> 43:01.663
Okay.

43:01.705 --> 43:07.002
So, one watches
and the other receives.

43:07.043 --> 43:09.963
Okay? Anton, you choose.

43:23.601 --> 43:24.728
(ZIPPER OPENS)

43:33.320 --> 43:37.657
REMEMBER: I love you.

43:38.908 --> 43:40.702
I love you.

43:48.501 --> 43:51.421
I don't even know why
you're going back up there.

43:51.463 --> 43:53.423
I just won't order
room service anymore.

43:53.465 --> 43:55.759
What does that even mean?

43:55.800 --> 43:58.970
Look, they've been watching me,
now I'm gonna watch them, okay?

43:59.012 --> 44:01.014
That's, that's a terrible idea.

44:01.056 --> 44:02.432
You want to come do it?

44:02.474 --> 44:04.225
Absolutely not. What?

44:04.267 --> 44:06.144
- That's what I thought.
- (DOORBELL RINGS)

44:06.186 --> 44:08.480
- All right, my food's here.
- Okay. I'll call you

44:08.521 --> 44:10.357
when I get back from Sacramento.

44:10.398 --> 44:12.734
- Yeah, okay, cool. Bye, cuckoo.
- Okay, bye.

44:12.776 --> 44:14.361
- (PHONE BEEPS)
- God.

44:14.402 --> 44:17.405
- (DOORBELL RINGS)
- Yes. Cool your jets!

44:43.515 --> 44:45.600
(INSECTS CHIRPING)

44:54.275 --> 44:56.277
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:06.204 --> 45:09.541
<i>♪ On a long-lost journey ♪</i>

45:09.582 --> 45:12.585
<i>♪ I'm going... ♪</i>

45:12.627 --> 45:15.338
ANTON: Me? Me?

45:15.380 --> 45:17.632
When Pocahontas bats
her eyelashes,

45:17.674 --> 45:19.634
you believe everything she says!

45:19.676 --> 45:21.594
- (GRUNTS)
- Don't call her what?

45:21.636 --> 45:24.472
Huh?! What?! What?!

45:24.514 --> 45:27.142
You're being a fucking asshole!
Fuck you!

45:27.183 --> 45:29.144
That's because
she didn't fucking do it!

45:29.185 --> 45:31.020
(DARIO SHOUTING)

45:40.864 --> 45:42.866
(COINS CLINKING)

46:01.759 --> 46:04.471
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

46:04.512 --> 46:06.514
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:09.684 --> 46:11.686
DEALER: Here we go, folks.

46:16.107 --> 46:17.358
MAGICIAN: Keep your eye on it.

46:17.400 --> 46:18.401
I know you are.

46:18.443 --> 46:19.944
With the big glasses, okay?
Watch this.

46:19.986 --> 46:21.529
There's nothing here.
(SHOUTS)

46:21.571 --> 46:23.531
(APPLAUSE IN DISTANCE)

46:36.544 --> 46:38.546
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:06.199 --> 47:08.576
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:08.618 --> 47:10.328
(KEYS JANGLE)

47:21.673 --> 47:23.466
(DOOR CLOSES)

47:23.508 --> 47:25.969
TEX RITTER: Some folks do
a lot of good in the world.

47:26.010 --> 47:28.596
That encourages us to do good.

47:28.638 --> 47:31.724
A few people start off
on the wrong foot.

47:31.766 --> 47:35.728
Their black deeds serve
as a warning post to us.

47:35.770 --> 47:38.898
The song I'm gonna sing
for you now, boys and girls,

47:38.940 --> 47:40.900
is about a boy
who sort of wandered off

47:40.942 --> 47:45.697
the straight and narrow trail,
took up a crooked course.

47:45.738 --> 47:47.991
As usual, with all outlaws,

47:48.032 --> 47:49.409
he paid with his life.

47:49.450 --> 47:52.662
His name was Billy the Kid.

47:52.704 --> 47:54.706
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:59.544 --> 48:04.966
<i>♪ I'll sing you a true song
of Billy the Kid ♪</i>

48:05.008 --> 48:10.555
<i>♪ I'll sing of the desperate
deeds that he did ♪</i>

48:10.597 --> 48:12.390
<i>♪ Just like poor Billy ♪</i>

48:12.432 --> 48:14.809
<i>♪ He wanders astray ♪</i>

48:14.851 --> 48:17.061
<i>♪ And loses his life ♪</i>

48:17.103 --> 48:22.066
<i>♪ In the very same way. ♪</i>

48:22.108 --> 48:24.402
Hey. Spencer Jackson.

48:24.444 --> 48:27.113
- Billy McBride.
- Yeah. Yeah, we've met before.

48:27.155 --> 48:28.531
Yeah, well,
I don't remember everything,

48:28.573 --> 48:30.408
but I-I hear
it was a wild night.

48:30.450 --> 48:33.411
(LAUGHS): Yeah. You are
a motherfucker, you know that?

48:33.453 --> 48:35.788
You got me so goddamn drunk
that night.

48:35.830 --> 48:37.790
Hell, I hadn't been
that wasted since college.

48:37.832 --> 48:40.376
Yeah, well, I have that effect
on people sometimes.

48:40.418 --> 48:42.295
(CHUCKLES): Yeah. Yeah.
And what about that, uh,

48:42.337 --> 48:44.380
that roulette chick
you were with? What's her story?

48:44.422 --> 48:46.090
- Well...
- How'd she win all that goddamn money?

48:46.132 --> 48:47.967
I guess the Rising Sun's
a good luck charm for her.

48:48.009 --> 48:49.844
- I don't know. You got me.
- (EXHALES): Oh, man.

48:49.886 --> 48:51.721
I fucking love that place, huh?

48:51.763 --> 48:53.765
- Yeah.
- It's a real shithole, but it's way out there

48:53.806 --> 48:55.933
and you do a lot of fun stuff
off the record,

48:55.975 --> 48:57.977
- you know?
- Oh, yeah, no doubt about that. Yeah, yeah.

48:58.019 --> 49:00.730
- So what can I do for you?
- Well, I'm an attorney,

49:00.772 --> 49:02.523
- and I...
- Uh-oh. What'd I do?

49:02.565 --> 49:04.776
- Uh, we'll see.
- (LAUGHS)

49:04.817 --> 49:07.528
No, uh, w-we've got
a class action lawsuit

49:07.570 --> 49:09.572
against the
Blackwood County Water Board.

49:09.614 --> 49:11.574
Oh.

49:11.616 --> 49:13.326
Well, how can I help you
with that?

49:13.368 --> 49:15.662
Well, I was hoping
to get some information

49:15.703 --> 49:17.455
about the Big Sur Agreement.

49:17.497 --> 49:20.875
- Big Sur?
- Yeah. Y-You were there, right?

49:20.917 --> 49:22.460
Well, sure,
I-I've been to Big Sur,

49:22.502 --> 49:24.295
but I don't know anything
about an agreement.

49:24.337 --> 49:26.881
Oh, right. Yeah, the NDAs.
Well, I'm gonna crack those.

49:26.923 --> 49:29.092
And when I do, I'm gonna find
out exactly who was there.

49:29.133 --> 49:31.886
Find out
who the big players were,

49:31.928 --> 49:33.513
and what each person's
got to lose.

49:33.554 --> 49:35.598
You know,
like reputation and career.

49:35.640 --> 49:37.767
Little shit like that. Yeah.

49:37.809 --> 49:40.269
If I were you, I'd think
about this long and hard.

49:40.311 --> 49:42.313
Figure out if you want to be
at the head of the train

49:42.355 --> 49:43.773
or the end of the train.

49:43.815 --> 49:45.608
Because as a representative
of the state,

49:45.650 --> 49:47.276
I'm pretty damn sure

49:47.318 --> 49:49.529
that I'm gonna find your name
on the dotted line

49:49.570 --> 49:54.200
as the guy who signed off on
privatizing a public resource.

49:54.242 --> 49:55.493
That ain't cool, you know?

49:55.535 --> 49:57.495
Well, Billy,
I have an 11:00, so...

49:57.537 --> 49:59.622
Oh, do you? That surprises
the shit out of me.

49:59.664 --> 50:02.291
- Yeah. I got work.
- (LAUGHS) Well, I'm not worried about it.

50:02.333 --> 50:04.711
You'll call me, as soon as you
find out that these fat cats

50:04.752 --> 50:06.713
you've been playing with,
these billionaires,

50:06.754 --> 50:10.091
they've got a whole team of
lawyers who are just salivating.

50:10.133 --> 50:12.301
They can't wait
to nail your goddamn ass

50:12.343 --> 50:13.720
and pin everything on you,

50:13.761 --> 50:16.931
so... I figure
I'll hear from you.

50:16.973 --> 50:20.059
I was gonna give you a card,
but... most of those guys

50:20.101 --> 50:22.854
have my number,
so you can get it pretty easy.

50:22.895 --> 50:24.897
You be good.

50:33.156 --> 50:34.365
(PHONE BEEPS)

50:36.409 --> 50:38.578
Wade? It's Spence.

50:38.619 --> 50:41.122
Uh, what the fuck is going on
in Blackwood County?

50:41.164 --> 50:42.957
BLACKWOOD (OVER PHONE): Hmm.
How do you mean?

50:42.999 --> 50:45.960
Well, Billy fucking McBride just
left my office is what I mean.

50:46.002 --> 50:47.879
- Oh, did he now?
- Yeah.

50:47.920 --> 50:51.716
Yeah. Just tell me this:
how worried do I need to be?

50:51.758 --> 50:53.718
(LAUGHS SOFTLY)

50:53.760 --> 50:58.014
Spencer wants to know
how worried he should be.

51:00.641 --> 51:03.019
He should be shaking
like a shitting dog

51:03.060 --> 51:05.271
on a thin sheet of ice.

51:05.313 --> 51:07.523
Wha... I-I, uh...

51:07.565 --> 51:08.941
- Feel better?
- Now, just...

51:08.983 --> 51:10.610
Can you shoot me straight,
please?

51:10.651 --> 51:12.987
Are we in trouble here?
Or are we good?

51:13.029 --> 51:16.115
(PHONE BEEPS)

51:16.157 --> 51:18.951
And what about me, Donald?

51:18.993 --> 51:23.956
When a rose as lovely
as you blooms,

51:23.998 --> 51:27.627
the bees come, uninvited.

51:27.668 --> 51:31.839
I will pin and mount

51:31.881 --> 51:34.717
every single one of them.

